-- Petrobras Overtakes Microsoft, Wal-Mart to Become Fouth-Largest Company
-- B y   D a v i d   P a p a d o p o u l o s
-- 2010-09-24T20:50:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/petrobras-jumps-to-fourth-biggest-company-in-world-after-sale.html
Petroleo Brasileiro SA, the
Brazilian state-run oil company, climbed to the fourth-biggest
company in the world by market value after its $70 billion share
sale yesterday, data compiled by Bloomberg shows.  Petrobras has a market value of $214 billion, more than
companies including Microsoft Corp. and Wal-Mart Stores Inc.
Only Exxon Mobil Corp., Apple Inc. and PetroChina Co. have
bigger market values, the data shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
